title: For Sale:  .50 Cal flintlock Plains Rifle muzzleloader
postcontent: Fullstock Plains Rifle, .50 caliber 36" barrel, iron, curly maple, and late Ketland flint lock.  This Plains rifle is stocked with iron furniture, single set trigger. The .50 caliber 15/16" octagon barrel is cut rifled with seven lands and grooves with a slow twist for a patched round ball. The barrel is a rich warm chocolate brown outside, and the rifled bore is bright and clean inside. This rifle has a 13-1/2" pull, to fit todays average shooter. The rifle weighs 8.9 pounds.  The triggerguard has a spoon like grip rail, typical of those found on Leman rifles.  This rifle uses a 1820 era Ketland flint lock. The lock has a worn brown patina finish. The “full waterproof pan" is made with rain gutters cut to drain any water away from the pan. The cock's jaws have been tipped down to throw sparks directly into the pan. The erect frizzen snaps over a roller bearing on the end of the frizzen spring, which is retained by an inside screw threaded into a blind hole in the bullet shaped spring finial. All features of late flintlocks. The trigger has a outside mounted spring. Push the trigger forward until it latches to "set" the trigger. This trigger must be set to cock the lock.  Fast ignition is assured by the Ampco vent liner, positioned well above the bottom of the pan, centered on the heat of the flash.  There are a few things about this gun you need to know.  The stock has a slight crack on side opposite the lockplate and a Lockplate bolt broke so I replaced it with one that works for now, but would need replaced to complete the look.  This gun has been used and expect that if you buy it.  I will also take trades on other blackpowder guns.  Bought this for $1600 5 years ago.  Open to offers and trades, even modern handgun, my price is flexible.  Can send more pictures if needed.  Willing to trade for blackpowder rifle.  Send me pictures of yours.  Would like civil war type gun.

The PMAG 30G utilizes a resilient Milspec black oxide coated stainless steel spring for corrosion resistance and an anti-tilt, self-lubricating follower for increased reliability. It is compatible with all PMAG floor plate accessories.

The PMAG 30G MagLevel features transparent windows on both sides of the body and has a painted indicator on the spring for quick determination of approximate rounds remaining in the magazine.

Compatible with all 5.56x45mm Heckler & Koch G36 variants, excluding the semi-auto U.S. marketed SL8.

Made in U.S.A.
